  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "There's a UI element, which at the moment is implemented in a bunch of different ways, but it might be worth to rethink how they are done. There's nothing wrong with having multiple components rendering similar variations of the same thing, but I'm seeing it being used in other places where more reusability could be beneficial.\r\n\r\nI don't have a good name for it yet, but it's an element that is used as navigation control as well as form control. Here are a few places where it's used:\r\n\r\nMost basic form (label + arrow [caret]):\r\n<img width=\"667\" alt=\"Screenshot 2021-04-20 at 09 49 21\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/445106/115358198-b3101a80-a1bd-11eb-8a06-adb6409aef4e.png\">\r\n\r\nSame but hovered state:\r\n<img width=\"667\" alt=\"Screenshot 2021-04-20 at 09 49 11\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/445106/115358255-c15e3680-a1bd-11eb-9129-4e767b449e96.png\">\r\n\r\nHere it has an additional supportive text, as well as useful and important information related to its data (also hovered):\r\n<img width=\"671\" alt=\"Screenshot 2021-04-20 at 09 50 58\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/445106/115358409-ea7ec700-a1bd-11eb-9a99-f99fba97b867.png\">\r\n\r\nWith badge:\r\n  <img width=\"653\" alt=\"Screenshot 2021-04-20 at 10 17 52\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/445106/115362304-adb4cf00-a1c1-11eb-9fec-aa6190378eac.png\">\r\n\r\nAs form control (can be radio, checkbox/switch etc), also hovered in this case:\r\n<img width=\"672\" alt=\"Screenshot 2021-04-20 at 09 51 19\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/445106/115358451-f79bb600-a1bd-11eb-93d6-f37eec6b7f12.png\">\r\n\r\nAs switch form control (hovered and idle):\r\n<img width=\"668\" alt=\"Screenshot 2021-04-20 at 09 48 29\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/445106/115358069-92e05b80-a1bd-11eb-8998-6a8fa2ba58a4.png\">\r\n<img width=\"667\" alt=\"Screenshot 2021-04-20 at 09 48 13\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/445106/115358084-983da600-a1bd-11eb-87d5-9294a8b31022.png\">\r\n\r\nHere's a different place in the app with practically the same element, but with an icon attached to it:\r\n<img width=\"470\" alt=\"Screenshot 2021-04-20 at 09 51 51\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/445106/115358509-0a15ef80-a1be-11eb-8252-114b37a2f1d4.png\">\r\n\r\n^ A few important notes on this last use case here:\r\n\r\n- While these are all the same, they are visually different (e.g. the ones above the divider have black font, the ones below have blue font, also the hover color is supposed to be different). We need to a good way to distinguish the two\r\n- The icons as of right now are implemented as `StatusRoundButton`, which is semantically wrong as those can't actually be clicked. We probably want to introduce a dedicated `StatusIcon` or StatusRoundIcon` component\r\n- The color of the icons has a level of transparency, so when the element is hovered, the color of the icon changes as well in relation to its parent hover color. This is something that isn't supported in `StatusRoundButton` either (another reason to not use it here)\r\n\r\nProfile menu items (although, this one is semantically very different than the others, so could be a separate component):\r\n<img width=\"307\" alt=\"Screenshot 2021-04-20 at 10 12 06\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/445106/115361434-e011fc80-a1c0-11eb-8d1c-d62a531b6f37.png\">\r\n\r\n\r\n## Proposal\r\n\r\nAt the moment, these components in the screenshots are implemented as:\r\n\r\n- `CommunityPopupButton` - (last screenshot) Not a good name for the component for various reasons. They don't always open a popup, they aren't always buttons but form controls, they aren't used just in community modals etc\r\n- `StatusSectionMenuItem` - (first screenshot) Also not a good name because it isn't used just in menu sections (but mostly). Also can't handle form controls (which is fine but it should still be more aligned with dedicated components then)\r\n- `StatusRadioButtonRow` - This thing is really just called a \"row\" because it was originally used in `Column` elements\r\n- `StatusSettingsLineButton` - Can be either a switch or just a the same thing that `StatusSectionMenuItem` is\r\n\r\n\r\nEssentially these components are either a button to navigate somewhere, or a form control to change some setting. They can be used within modals, pages, setting sections etc.\r\n\r\nI propose we introduce the following components respectively:\r\n\r\n### `StatusSectionButton`\r\n\r\n```qml\r\nStatusSectionButton {\r\n  text: \"Chat preview links\"\r\n  hint: \"Supportive text\" // default: \"\" - not rendered when empty\r\n  value: \"None\"\r\n  hasBadge: false // default: false - renders `value` inside of badge instead of text\r\n  showArrow: true // default: true - Can be disabled when used in profile menu context\r\n  icon.name: \"edit\" // default: \"\" - Will be resolved by component, if empty, no icon is rendered\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\n**Additional thoughts:**\r\n\r\nStill need a way to configure whether we want a \"round\" icon or an icon without background (like it's done in the profile menu section). If the profile menu items are becoming completely different elements, then this can be omitted. Otherwise we'd have to maybe at `icon.bgColor` which defaults to `transparent`, but that would force us to override it with a color when we do want to have a round icon (makes it impractical when it comes to theming). So alternatively we could have `StatusSectionButtonWithIcon` and `StatusSectionButtonWithRoundIcon` respectively. The API would look exactly the same as `StatusSectionButton` just that it has the \"round\" encoded into it.\r\n\r\n### `StatusSectionRadioControl`, `StatusSectionSwitchControl`\r\n\r\n```qml\r\nStatusSectionRadioControl {\r\n  text: \"Chat preview links\"\r\n  hint: \"Supportive text\"\r\n  checked: false // default: false\r\n}\r\n\r\nStatusSectionSwitchControl {\r\n  text: \"Chat preview links\"\r\n  hint: \"Supportive text\"\r\n  checked: false // default: false\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nSame thoughts about icons apply here as well.\r\n\r\n## Needs discussion\r\n\r\nAs mentioned above, in the case of the community modal, there's multiple variants of the same component that are exactly the same functionality-wise, but are rendered in different colors and hover effects. We need to encode that somehow. Maybe with a property `variant` that can be individually configured?",
