    "body": "> I guess StatusSectionRadioControl and StatusSectionSwitchControl would use StatusSectionButton? It might not be possible, but if we could, it could make it even less duplicated.\r\n\r\nThanks! Correct, form controls and buttons are two different types of components. Despite it being hard/impossible to have a component be an actual `Button` and something else at the same time, I believe that we're better off composing components from smaller ones anyways.\r\n\r\n> As for the community buttons needing different colors, if need be, we can always just expose aliases or properties to change those from the exterior as to not create new components just for a color change for example.\r\n\r\nThat's true. Would vote for that as well, but we need to be selective what components we want to expose and don't just have a one-component-to-fit-all case, where one compnoent has a radio, a switch, a this, a that, and we expose all of them, while only one of them is used at a time. It would make the component unnecessarily complex (see `StatusButton` as one example for that)",
